 rather than a remote one. When using `ray.init(address=\"host:port\")` without the `ray://` prefix, Ray might be interpreting this differently and looking for local session metadata files instead of connecting to the remote address.\n\nI should try using the proper Ray Client protocol with `ray://ray-head:10001` to explicitly connect as a client to the remote cluster, or check if there's a stale Ray session on the pod that's interfering with the connection attempt. I should test a few different connection approaches to see which one actually works. Let me start by checking if there's already a Ray process running on the client pod, then try connecting with the original address format first before switching to the alternative methods.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1001,"cache_read_input_tokens":31988,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1001},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0ef2fc7-7393-4b56-9859-67257b72123a","uuid":"70d579ce-06db-4756-99a1-79757a710b96","request_id":"req_011CcMVpWcLHMsXaUszQUqvj"}
